jobs_results.title: Digital Layout Designer
jobs_results.description:
Summary

Do you have a passion for crafting entirely new solutions? As part of our Digital Design Engineering group, you’ll take imaginative and revolutionary ideas and determine how to turn them into reality! You and your team will apply engineering fundamentals and start from scratch if needed, bringing forward-thinking ideas to the real world. Your efforts will be groundbreaking. Join us, and you’ll help design the tools that allow us to bring customers experiences they’ve never before envisioned. You will be part of an exciting silicon design group that is responsible for designing state-of-the-art ASICs. We have an extraordinary opportunity for Digital Layout Technical Lead! In this highly visible role as senior member of Apple’s custom layout team, you will be working on the latest technology nodes to create world-class custom digital macros and libraries. As a technical lead, you will be responsible for leading layout design activities and methodologies and manage a small team... of layout designers. This is a fast-paced work environment with endless learning opportunities working in the design team with members of integration, CAD, circuit, and technology engineering.

Key Qualifications

We are looking for applicants with 10 years hands-on experience in custom layout design of deep SubMicron CMOS circuits used in high performance microprocessors.

Proven experience in developing, driving and implementing layout methodologies.

Strong influence and negotiation skills.

Excellent interpersonal skills and able to work with multi-functional teams.

Experience designing low noise, low power data paths, standard cells and large memory blocks.

High-level proficiency in layout floor planning, standard cell planning and hierarchical layout assembly.

Ability to recognize failure prone circuit and layout structures and actively work with circuit designers for the best approach to resolve problems.

Ability to estimate the design work for an assignment.

Scripting skills in CSH, PERL or SKILL are preferred.

Ability to understand issues of RC delay, IR, electro migration, cross and self-heating.

Description

Imagine yourself at the center of our SOC design effort, collaborating with all fields, playing a strategic role of getting functional products to millions of customers quickly. You will have the opportunity to integrate and come-up with new ideas, as well as work with a team of hardworking engineers. As a member of the layout team of the microprocessor group, you will be responsible to drive convergence of layout designs by: - Define, develop and drive new and innovative layout methodologies to improve layout productivity and quality for the digital team. - Oversee, mentor and lead a small layout group and remote contractors. - Represent the layout team to influence tool vendors, CAD management and design management to define and implement the technical direction of tools and flows. - Evaluate all aspects of the process flow from high-level design to transistor level layout. - Define and drive layout research assignments to influence new methodology in the organization. - Work with layout, design and management teams to influence the technical direction of designs across the organization. - Mentor and coach circuit and layout designers on layout standard methodologies. - Work with management and circuit design teams to plan, schedule work and negotiate any necessary layout trade-offs that impact design.

Education & Experience

BS Degree, or equivalent.

Additional Requirements

Apple is an Equal Opportunity Employer that is committed to inclusion and diversity. We also take affirmative action to offer employment and advancement opportunities to all applicants, including minorities, women, protected veterans, and individuals with disabilities. Apple will not discriminate or retaliate against applicants who inquire about, disclose, or discuss their compensation or that of other applicants.

jobs_results.title: Digital Designer
jobs_results.description:
About Us

Peak Design is a carry brand: we design bags and accessories that help people better carry, organize, and access their stuff. We launch our products on Kickstarter, where we’ve raised over $30M across 9 projects. We’re entirely crowdfunded—no outside investors—and that gives us the freedom to focus on the things that matter most to us: designing the best products, fostering happy employees, and taking care of our customers and natural environment. There are currently 36 of us. We love our jobs, we love each other, and we couldn’t be more stoked for the future of our company.

We also believe a diverse team is an innovative team and something worth celebrating. A range of perspectives and backgrounds creates a stronger and more creative work environment (not to mention more fun). We’re committed to equality and inclusivity across race, gender, age, religion, identity, and experience.

We are adding a digital designer to our team, and we hope it’s you! We need the eye of a... graphic designer, the chops/skills of a web designer, and the intuition of a UX designer. You would be joining our close-knit graphics/branding team to keep the look and feel of Peak Design one of the sharpest in the world of outdoor gear and product design.

YOUR DELIVERABLES
• Chief among your responsibilities would be spearheading projects related to our website. Peakdesign.com is the beating heart of our business, and it is always being tweaked in ways big and small.
• There are plenty of other projects that need TLC, as well: packaging design, in-store experience design, advertising campaigns, digital and print assets for various channels, general brand strategy.
• Identifying problems and places for improvement and then working with other teams (at Peak and externally) to bring those projects to life.
YOUR SKILLS
• You are passionate about web design. You fiddle with html and css, you're familiar with Figma, you can use Adobe Creative suite in your sleep, you're great at concepting, wireframing, and interfacing with engineers/developers. (gasp!)
• You are a great communicator, written and verbally. You can design but you can also talk about design.
• You are disciplined, organized, inquisitive and driven. We operate with as little structure as possible and our team is increasingly dispersed, you are a self starter that can turn a vague idea into a tangible asset with limited input.
• Obsession with detail but commitment to larger, strategic vision.
• Ability to quickly turn feedback into design changes.
PERKS!
• Work from Home!
• Flexible work schedule
• Comprehensive medical, mental, dental, and vision benefits for you and your family
• 401(k) retirement plan that allows pre-tax, Roth, and after-tax contributions with an employer match.
• Employee Purchase Program
• FSA, HSA, Commuter Benefits
• Career development reimbursement (classes, conferences, workshops of your choosing)
• Unlimited paid vacation
• HRA Fertility Benefits including egg freezing
• 100% paid parental leave
• Annual 2-3 day company retreat
• and more

jobs_results.title: Digital Design Engineer
jobs_results.description:
Summary

Join our team at Apple developing custom mixed-signal integrated circuits for Apple’s existing and future product lines! We've already shipped hundreds of millions of chips into several Apple product lines, including new products launched this year!

As a member of our mixed-signal ASIC team, you will be responsible for crafting sophisticated digital IPs for Apple power conversion and management IC’s. You will work with the system architects, product teams, verification engineers, and analog designers, creating block level specifications and implementing the designs. You will own the creation of the blocks, and take them through the concept, implementation, and validation phases, and then into mass production. Learn and use state of the art digital and mixed-signal tools and development flows to implement your designs.

We supply silicon to most of Apple’s industry leading hardware development teams. We have a close-knit, robust team in need of experience digital design... engineers to lead the development of new IPs and mentor junior engineers entering the mixed signal ASIC development field. Join us in building Apple’s next generation products. Do you want to be a part of building the “surprise and delight” in Apple’s future products?

Key Qualifications

Ten or more years developing digital IP’s for SoC’s or mixed signal IC’s.

Experience mentoring or leading junior design or verification engineers.

Proven track record shipping quality designs on schedule.

Experience with synthesis and static timing tools.

Expertise in Clock Domain Crossing design and verification techniques.

Experience with power estimation tools and techniques.

Familiarity with silicon development milestones and project resource management.

Solid understanding of low power design techniques, including clock and power gating.

Familiarity with UPF based power intent specification and power verification.

Some familiarity with mix-signal ASIC design and asynchronous analog / digital interfaces is helpful, but not required.

Description

• Deliver complex digital control blocks, meeting schedule, area, power, and performance targets.

• Collaborate in developing precise design specifications for digital control blocks.

• Implement FSM’s and other control logic in System Verilog.

• Collaborate with managers and program managers to track progress and gauge tapeout readiness.

• Work with DV teams to create verification plans.

• Work with silicon validation team in developing lab validation and qualification plans.

• Work with test team in developing implementation plans for ATE test programs.

Education & Experience

BSEE/MSEE preferred.

jobs_results.title: Digital Ads Graphic Designer
jobs_results.description:
The Digital Ads Graphic Designer Role

We are seeking an accomplished Digital Ads Graphic Designer to take our PPC campaigns to the next level. This role will be a part of our rapidly growing team of professionals responsible for creating and optimizing our graphics to ensure our brand resonates with our target audiences on Facebook and Instagram. The Digital Ads Graphic Designer will constantly push not only their creativity on design but test the response to their designs through proven data strategies.

About Us

AMMD is AmyMyersMD.com, a CPG e-commerce wellness platform that’s a respected resource for people seeking to get to the root of their health issues, find solutions, and take control of their health. An innovative market leader, AMMD aims to inspire a healthier, more informed world where chronic illness is a thing of the past and our tools are used by millions around the world to achieve optimal health.

Founded in 2017 by Dr. Amy Myers, a former Peace Corps Volunteer... emergency physician, functional medicine expert, and 2x New York Times bestselling author, AMMD is driven by her passion for empowering people to achieve their best selves. AMMD was named to the Inc. 5000 list of fastest-growing American companies in 2018 and 2019 and was an Inc. 5000 Regional Winner in 2020.

We’re proud to be a gamechanger in the health and wellness industry. A nimble digital marketing company, we use the latest tools and research to deliver the very best in everything we do. Through our high-quality, physician-formulated nutritional supplements, proven, step-by-step programs, thoroughly-researched information, and world-class customer care, we serve the health needs of hundreds of thousands of people in 122 countries around the globe.

About You

You love to push creative boundaries and find unique ways to stop the scroll and drive the click. Your love for graphic design lives alongside your passion for social media campaigns with outstanding click through rates. You thrive in an evolving work environment while keeping order to your workflow. Your ideal day is equal parts creative, data-driven, and task-oriented to hit project deadlines.

What you’ll do
• Create compelling, cohesive, and on-brand designs across all PPC channels with a specific focus on Facebook & social media advertising but also includes:
• Search (Google, Bing, Amazon)
• Display (Criteo, Google, FB, Amazon)
• Additional channels as they arise
• Iterate and optimize split test variations based on data to ensure that designs maximize clicks and conversions on Facebook and other platforms
• Maintain solid brand guidelines across ads
• Utilize the team file structure and naming conventions so that design files can be easily located and updated
• Take immense pride in your work and demonstrate your passion about improving your craft and skills
• Bring fresh ideas to the table and stay up-to-date on design trends in Facebook, PPC, display & native advertising
• Stay focused and on task with minimal oversight or direction
• Practice open, honest, and supportive communication
• Think critically and proactively problem solve
• Excel in a rapidly growing and dynamic environment

Knowledge, Skills, Abilities
• 3-5 years as a graphic designer with hands-on experience in digital advertising (Facebook ad design experience is a must)
• Expertise in Adobe Creative Suite (Photoshop, InDesign, Illustrator)
• A strong foundation of design fundamentals - typography, layout, color, etc
• Familiarity with best practices in digital advertising (PPC) design across all devices
• Track record of high-quality designs delivered on time
• Understanding of marketing terminology (call to action, conversion, etc.)
• Experience designing for direct response and e-commerce marketing

Why People Love Working Here
• Office at our new, state of the art campus, centrally located near Southpark Meadows in Austin, Texas
• Flexible WFH scheduling
• 15 days of annual Flex Time, starting day one
• Comprehensive medical, dental, vision, and 401k benefits
• Family-friendly work environment and events
• Monthly happy hours
• Team building events
• 45% discount on all AMMD products so you can live the solution
• In office smoothie bar, coffee, and fresh snacks

Important Information

How to get your application noticed: Apply online here or our website (https://ammd.applytojob.com/apply).

Location: This is a full-time, Austin-based position. We’re located in south Austin near I-35 and Slaughter Lane in the Southpark Meadows area.

Verification: In compliance with federal law, all persons hired will be required to verify identity and eligibility to work in the United States and to complete the required employment eligibility verification form upon hire
